<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-59-0285 </DOCNO><TEXT>A survey is presented of the national policies of 15 countries on dealingwith radioactive wastes arising from nuclear power programmes. Althoughthere is a wide measure of agreement on how the different radioactivewastes can best be dealt with safely, there are significant variationsin policy and timing between countries. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>